{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "pi-vimmode already supports a finite semantic keymap, protected Pi shortcut delegation, Ex command-line mode, transient Ex messages, settings validation warnings, and user-facing feature/settings docs. The confusing gap is explainability: keymap validation can reject fields, lifecycle can show `vim \u26a0`, protected shortcuts can delegate, and many no-op inputs can invalidate silently, but users do not have a runtime way to ask what happened or what actions are available. Current seams:"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 15", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Give users compact runtime answers for \u201cwhy is `vim \u26a0` showing?\u201d, \u201cwhat does this key do?\u201d, \u201cwhy can\u2019t I map this Pi shortcut?\u201d, and \u201cwhat actions exist?\u201d."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 32", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### 1. Add a pure customization metadata/helper seam Target seams: new `src/customization.ts` (or equivalent), plus `src/config.ts`, `src/commands.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, and tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_1_add_a_pure_customization_metadata_helper_seam", "label": "1. Add a pure customization metadata/helper seam", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 34", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: new `src/customization.ts` (or equivalent), plus `src/config.ts`, `src/commands.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, and tests. Create a pure module that exposes:"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_2_keep_diagnostic_ex_commands_finite_and_read_only", "label": "2. Keep diagnostic Ex commands finite and read-only", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 51", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`. Extend the finite Ex parser with read-only commands:"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_3_generalize_the_transient_message_model_without_adding_a_pager", "label": "3. Generalize the transient message model without adding a pager", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 71", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`. Add or rename message state to support `kind: \"error\" | \"success\" | \"info\"` and text from both Ex and optional no-op feedback. Preserve current Ex row behavior: one width-fitted row below the prompt, clearing on next handled input."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_4_preserve_diagnostics_from_settings_load_into_live_editors", "label": "4. Preserve diagnostics from settings load into live editors", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 86", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/lifecycle.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, `src/config.ts`, tests. Carry settings diagnostics alongside resolved options from lifecycle to each `VimEditor` instance. `:vimdoctor` reads the retained diagnostics instead of re-reading or mutating settings."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_5_add_presets_as_typed_settings_baselines_before_explicit_fields", "label": "5. Add presets as typed settings baselines before explicit fields", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 99", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/types.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `docs/settings.md`, tests. Add `piVimMode.preset?: \"minimal\" | \"prompt-safe\" | \"vim-heavy\"`. Presets provide option baselines. Explicit fields from the same settings object override the selected preset. Project settings continue to override global settings field-by-field."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_6_keep_optional_no_op_feedback_off_by_default_and_narrowly_scoped", "label": "6. Keep optional no-op feedback off by default and narrowly scoped", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 122", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/types.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, docs/tests. Add a setting such as `piVimMode.feedback.noop` with accepted values that default to quiet behavior. When enabled, only confusing no-ops produce transient info/error messages, such as protected shortcut delegation, invalid pending operator/motion, empty redo stack, or an unmapped key in normal mode. Routine safe misses should not flood output."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 135", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Protected shortcut catalog can drift from runtime delegation \u2192 use one exported catalog/helper from config and modal runtime tests. - Preset merge order can discard sibling settings \u2192 add config tests for global/project preset plus explicit overrides, invalid preset fallback, and live editor option propagation via `cloneOptions`. - One-row diagnostics can be too terse \u2192 keep commands searchable and link docs; defer multi-line pager to a later Ex display/help change."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_ref_src_config_ts", "label": "config.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_ref_src_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 8", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_ref_src_commands_ts", "label": "commands.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 9", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_ref_src_ex_ts", "label": "ex.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 10", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_ref_src_modal_engine_ts", "label": "engine.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 11", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-self-explaining-customization-suite/design.md", "source_location": "line 15", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_04_self_explaining_customization_suite_design